About IBCIBC Corporate Presentation 
Download Presentation: Please click the “share” icon on the bottom right of the presentation. You may then email the presentation and download at your convenience. IBC Advanced Alloys Corp. ("IBC") (TSXV:IB, OTCQB:IAALF) IBC is a leading beryllium and copper advanced alloys company serving a variety of industries such as defense, aerospace, automotive, telecommunications, precision manufacturing, and others. IBC's Copper Division manufactures and distributes a variety of copper alloys as castings and forgings, including beryllium copper, chrome copper, and aluminum bronze.  IBC's Engineered Materials Division makes the Beralcast® family of alloys, which can be precision cast and are used in an increasing number of defense, aerospace, and other systems, including the F-35 Joint Strike Fighter. IBC's has production facilities in Indiana, Massachusetts, Pennsylvania, and Missouri.  The Company's common shares are traded on the TSX Venture Exchange under the symbol "IB" and the OTCQB under the symbol "IAALF".  IBC: 1. Product research to stimulate demand (including nuclear fuels R&D).2. Downstream manufacturing and distribution with two divisions: Copper Alloys (Franklin, IN) and Engineered Materials (Wilmington, MA).
 





